00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:45,556
Fill it full of rocket fuel and come get me.

241
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:48,314
[WHISPERS]
I'll leave the door unlocked.

242
00:13:50,240 --> 00:13:51,798
Maybe you should talk to someone.

243
00:13:51,959 --> 00:13:54,029
Let them know
you're having a little anxiety.

244
00:13:54,199 --> 00:13:58,272
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
No, no. I'm ﬁne. No anxiety.

245
00:13:58,439 --> 00:14:00,191
We should probably talk in code.

246
00:14:00,360 --> 00:14:04,353
From now on, "frog" is me, "sandwich"
means you, and "lemon" means rocket.

247
00:14:04,519 --> 00:14:08,432
So come on, sandwich, build me a lemon
because froggie wants to come home.

248
00:14:13,639 --> 00:14:15,197
Look at you...

249
00:14:15,399 --> 00:14:17,674
...putting on a brave face.

250
00:14:18,439 --> 00:14:20,828
There's nothing to be brave about.
Everything's fine.

251
00:14:20,999 --> 00:14:24,275
Really? I don't know how much
you know about primate behavior...

252
00:14:24,439 --> 00:14:27,556
...but Sheldon's assistant
was clearly courting Leonard.

253
00:14:27,759 --> 00:14:29,795
Were she a mandrill,
she would've bent over...

254
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:34,112
...and displayed her brightly colored
hindquarters like a big red welcome mat.

255
00:14:35,879 --> 00:14:39,235
By the way, you try that
at the junior prom, you get kicked out.

256
00:14:40,999 --> 00:14:44,196
Okay, maybe she was flirting with him,
but who cares?

257
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:47,158
I don't even know where
my relationship is with Leonard now.

258
00:14:47,319 --> 00:14:48,991
So says your prefrontal cortex.

259
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:51,549
But the limbic system of your brain
is calculating...

260
00:14:51,719 --> 00:14:54,074
...that if another woman is attracted
to Leonard...

261
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,992
...it must be because he's desirable.

262
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:59,391
Well, of course he's desirable.
I mean, he's great.

263
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:02,279
He's smart, he's sweet,
and in the bedroom, whew...

264
00:15:02,439 --> 00:15:05,954
...let me tell you, he really tries.

265
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,595
So it does bother you.

266
00:15:09,759 --> 00:15:12,148
Fine, it bothers me a little.

267
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:15,633
No, you know what? This is stupid.
It doesn't bother me.

268
00:15:16,519 --> 00:15:18,111
Okay, it bothers me.

269
00:15:19,400 --> 00:15:22,949
But only because she wouldn't
stop laughing. Leonard is not that funny.

270
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:25,634
And there you have it...

271
00:15:25,839 --> 00:15:28,592
...prefrontal-cortex reasoning
versus limbic lust.

272
00:15:29,279 --> 00:15:31,509
If this were a boxing match
they might call it...

273
00:15:31,679 --> 00:15:33,476
...the Thriller Adjacent to the Amygdala.

274
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:35,550
[LAUGHING]

275
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:41,870
If you were a brain scientist,
you would be busting a gut right now.

276
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:47,553
-So how was work today?
-Oh, it was all right, I guess.

277
00:15:47,719 --> 00:15:50,791
Had to Heimlich a cherry stem
out of Sheldon.

278
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,875
-Caught Raj right in the eye.
-Oh.

279
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,714
-You're kidding.
-No, Raj had to go to the nurse.

280
00:15:57,879 --> 00:16:00,313
Wow. Anything else?

281
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:04,189
Mm, the nurse is a woman,
so he couldn't talk to her.

282
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:08,469
She had to bring him the Grover puppet
so he could point at what hurt. Heh.

283
00:16:12,159 --> 00:16:13,797
Is that it?

284
00:16:13,999 --> 00:16:15,876
Isn't that enough?

285
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:19,510
It had weaponized fruit and a puppet.
What more do you want?

286
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:21,593
Oh, good. Leonard, you're here.

287
00:16:21,759 --> 00:16:23,954
Science news. This will interest you.

288
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,680
And, Penny, feel free to paint your nails.

289
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:30,748
-What do you got?
-I believe Alex may have unearthed...

290
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:34,833
...the grade-school science project
that could be my ticket to the Nobel Prize.

291
00:16:34,999 --> 00:16:36,352
Behold.

292
00:16:36,519 --> 00:16:38,669
"Magnets: What Do They Stick To?"

293
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:44,315
If the answer is metal,
it's not exactly groundbreaking.

294
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,549
The original title was:

295
00:16:45,719 --> 00:16:49,268
"A Rederivation of Maxwell's Equations
Regarding Electromagnetism."

296
00:16:49,439 --> 00:16:52,636
l dumbed it down because some
of the more religious people in town...

297
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:55,234
...were starting to say I was a witch.

298
00:16:55,879 --> 00:16:58,837
Sheldon thinks the approach
in his paper might change the way...

299
00:16:58,999 --> 00:17:03,789
-...we calculate ferromagnetic hysteresis.
-Oh. It's about time. I hated the old way.

300
00:17:04,639 --> 00:17:06,311
-Hi, I'm Penny.
-Alex.

301
00:17:06,479 --> 00:17:09,312
-Do you work with Dr. Hofstadter?
-In a way.

302
00:17:11,799 --> 00:17:15,155
We've kind of been involved
in a five-year experiment.

303
00:17:15,319 --> 00:17:17,753
Oh. Well, you're lucky.
He seems very talented.

304
00:17:17,919 --> 00:17:19,989
I'm sure a lot of people
wanna work with him.

305
00:17:20,159 --> 00:17:22,992
Oh, well, a lot of people can't, so....

306
00:17:23,679 --> 00:17:25,476
Uh, come on.

307
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:27,034
Where are we going?

308
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:30,272
My limbic system
wants to take your pants off.

309
00:17:33,279 --> 00:17:34,917
She seems nice.

310
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:37,150
Notice people on your own time.
We're working.

311
00:17:43,559 --> 00:17:45,151
Hey, Howie, how you feeling?

312
00:17:45,319 --> 00:17:47,037
HOWARD [OVER COMPUTER]:
Better. Much better.

313
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:52,832
The other astronauts held me down
and gave me a shot.

314
00:17:58,119 --> 00:18:00,155
Ooh.

315
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,234
Attention, people of Earth.

316
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:09,919
Tonight there will be two moons
in the sky.

317
00:18:10,119 --> 00:18:11,996
Howie, stop that.

318
00:18:12,159 --> 00:18:13,911
NASA's watching this.

319
00:18:14,079 --> 00:18:16,468
Put your pants back on.

